title: Butch Cassidy and the Sundance Kid  (2013 - Unabridged)
description:
Audio Books : History : MP3/Variable : English


The Last Outlaws: The Lives and Legends of Butch Cassidy and the Sundance Kid (Audiobook) By Thom Hatch, read by James C. Lewis
Unabridged edition 2013 | 9 hours and 53 mins | ISBN: 1452610452 | MP3 160 kbps | 714 MB



Butch Cassidy and the Sundance Kid planned and executed the most daring robbies of the Old West, targeting banks, railroads and mines. As the sun rose on the twentieth century, they could not outrun the rapid growth of new techonolgy and sprawling cities that altered the landscape and their very way of life. With high prices on their heads, Butch and Sundance fled to South America, where they supposedly met their deaths in a blaze of glory. This biography traces the lives and mysterious deaths of two Wild West icons who defied a nation.
